" The human body is a complex biological system composed of cells, tissues, organs, and organ systems working together to maintain life. It is structured hierarchically, beginning at the chemical level and organized into several major systems that handle distinct physiological functions.Organ Systems The body functions through 11 major organ systems: Skeletal System: Composed of 206 bones in an adult, it provides structural support, protects internal organs, stores minerals like calcium, and produces blood cells within the bone marrow. Muscular System: Consists of skeletal, smooth, and cardiac muscles. It enables voluntary body movement, facilitates involuntary movements like digestion, and generates body heat. Nervous System: Includes the brain, spinal cord, and nerves. It acts as the body's control center, processing sensory information, regulating rapid responses, and managing higher cognitive functions.Endocrine System: Made up of glands such as the pituitary, thyroid, and adrenals that secrete hormones into the blood to regulate long-term processes like metabolism, growth, and reproduction.Cardiovascular System: Comprises the heart, blood vessels, and blood. It transports oxygen, nutrients, hormones, and waste products throughout the body.Lymphatic and Immune System: Composed of lymph nodes, the spleen, thymus, and white blood cells. It returns leaked fluid to the bloodstream and defends the body against pathogens and infections.Respiratory System: Includes the lungs, trachea, and airways. It is responsible for taking in oxygen from the air and expelling carbon dioxide waste.Digestive System: Contains the mouth, esophagus, stomach, intestines, liver, and pancreas. It breaks down food mechanically and chemically, absorbs nutrients, and eliminates solid waste. Urinary System: Composed of the kidneys, ureters, bladder, and urethra. It filters waste products from the blood, regulates fluid and electrolyte balance, and excretes urine. Integumentary System: Formed by the skin, hair, and nails. It serves as the primary protective barrier against environmental damage, helps regulate temperature, and contains sensory receptors.Reproductive System: Differs between biological males and females; its primary purpose is the production of gametes (sperm and eggs) and hormones to enable human reproduction."